Patch: miso 1.11 / GHC 9.14 RTS bring-up contract for the upstream
haskell-miso/{chess,solitaire}.git launcher.

The upstream static/index.js predates miso 1.11 / GHC 9.14 and is
missing two pieces the current RTS requires:

  1. @bjorn3/browser_wasi_shim must be >= 0.4.2 — the WASI import set
     changed between 0.3.0 and 0.4.x; on 0.3.0 our wasm module fails
     to instantiate against this shim.

  2. instance.exports.__ghc_wasm_jsffi_init() MUST be invoked between
     wasi.initialize(instance) and the first hs_start() call. Without
     it the RTS panics:
        [WASI stderr] newBoundTask: RTS is not initialised;
                      call hs_init() first
     and the wasm module exits before miso ever mounts to <body>.

The chess + solitaire repos ship the identical static/index.js, so a
single patch fits both. Once they update their launcher upstream this
file can be retired.

(GNU patch ignores everything above the first `--- a/...` header, so
this preamble passes straight through.)

--- a/static/index.js
+++ b/static/index.js
@@ -1,5 +1,5 @@
 
-import { WASI, OpenFile, File, ConsoleStdout } from "https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@bjorn3/browser_wasi_shim@0.3.0/dist/index.js";
+import { WASI, OpenFile, File, ConsoleStdout } from "https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@bjorn3/browser_wasi_shim@0.4.2/dist/index.js";
 import ghc_wasm_jsffi from "./ghc_wasm_jsffi.js";
 
 const args = [];
@@ -20,5 +20,6 @@
 Object.assign(instance_exports, instance.exports);
 
 wasi.initialize(instance);
+instance.exports.__ghc_wasm_jsffi_init();
 await instance.exports.hs_start(globalThis.example);
 
